'''Adam Marian Tomasz Pius Leon duke [[Korybut]] Woroniecki''', [[religious name]] '''Jacek''' (December 21, 1878 in Lublin &ndash; May 18, 1949 in Kraków) was a Polish [[Servant of God]].

He was a priest and member of the [[Dominican Order]], [[theologian]], [[teacher]], [[professor]] of [[ethics]] and [[scholasticism|scholastic philosopher]]. He was also the [[Rector (academia)|rector]] of the [[Katolicki Uniwersytet Lubelski]] (the Catholic University of Lublin) from 1922 to 1924, a member of [[Polska Akademia Umiejętności]] (the Polish Academy of Learning), [[professor]] of the [[Angelicum]] and the founder of [[Zgromadzenie Sióstr Dominikanek Misjonarek Jezusa i Maryi]] (the Congregation of Sisters Dominicans Missionaries of Jesus and Mary).

